      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For international business, the standard is usually conservative, leaning towards classic tailoring that is universally accepted. Men should stick to dark, well-fitted suits with muted ties, while women should opt for tailored dresses or pant suits in professional colors. The key is always quality over trendiness, ensuring everything is perfectly pressed and fits impeccably. Avoid anything overly flashy or revealing, as those choices are rarely perceived as sophisticated in a global corporate setting.",
      "source": "target",
