      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In those regions, showing respect for local customs is paramount, and a Western suit might be too stiff or inappropriate depending on the specific event. Incorporating elements of local formal wear, or at least dressing in high-quality, modest attire that respects the local culture, is far more sophisticated. For instance, in some parts of Asia, a well-tailored traditional garment can convey more respect and gravitas than a standard Western suit. Always observe what the most established local professionals are wearing to gauge the appropriate level of formality.",
